  "texts": [
    "The simulation was performed in the following order: first, the entire system, including both the water droplet and the silica substrate, was gradually heated from 1 to 300 K in four stages using temperature rescaling, followed by 1.2 ns of thermalization at 300 K in the NVT ensemble.",
    "Next, it was performed in the NVT ensemble for 10 ns.",
    "The pressure was not explicitly constrained, as well as in all other systems simulated in this study.",
    "This choice was motivated by the fact that local pressure fluctuations in nanoscale systems reach hundreds of atmospheres, largely exceeding the effect of moderate external pressure variations.",
    "Therefore, applying an external barostat was considered unnecessary."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}